review_blob: Its just so mind blowingly good. Bourbon taste is super strong but it works so well with the beer. Its one of the best bourbon barrel beers I have ever had. Its freakishly delicious.
beer_name: Central Waters Brewers Reserve Bourbon Barrel Barleywine

review_blob: Holy taste of alcohol Batman. Started off a bit like I was drinking rubbing alcohol but that mellowed as it warmed and the hoppiness started to come through. Not an awesome DIPA for this reviewer.
Nitro pour at Nobi. Decent stout. One of those "I am glad I tried it but probably wont have another" beers. The gals behind the bar at Nobi know their shit.
beer_name: Lone Pint Knecht Ruprecht I: Dark Chocolate Coffee Milk Stout

review_blob: Draft at DTW. Really good ipa, citrus forward and delicious. I had never heard of this one and glad I had time during my layover to have one!

Huge fan of this seasonal usually, this year is the rare year it disappoints. Smell is not fresh, sorta stanky but not good stanky. Funky stanky. Flavor is just flat, no juice to this one. I love you Surly, but this one missed the mark for me this year.
Astounding. Exactly what I like in an ipa, bright citrus hop flavor, and pours a true pint out of a can. World class.
In what I feel is a weak season if fresh/wet/harvest beers this one stands out. Very enjoyable, crisp fresh taste. Outstanding.
